definitions: Made something free of dirt, marks, or unwanted matter.
Removed the internal organs from an animal, especially a fish or bird, in preparation for cooking.
Emptied or cleared out a place or container.
Made a profit or gained a large amount of money, often illicitly.
examples: She cleaned the entire house before the guests arrived.
He cleaned the fish he caught by the river.
They cleaned out the garage over the weekend.
The gang cleaned up on the illegal gambling operation.
